Marathi and Hindi

                            apertium-mar-hin
===============================================================================

This is an Apertium language pair for translating between Marathi and
Hindi. What you can use this language package for:

* Translating between Marathi and Hindi
* Morphological analysis of Marathi and Hindi
* Part-of-speech tagging of Marathi and Hindi

For information on the latter two points, see subheading "For more
information" below

Requirements
===============================================================================

You will need the following software installed:

* lttoolbox (>= 3.3.0)
* apertium (>= 3.3.0)
* vislcg3 (>= 0.9.9.10297)
* apertium-hin
* apertium-mar

If this does not make any sense, we recommend you look at: www.apertium.org

Compiling
===============================================================================

Given the requirements being installed, you should be able to just run:

$ ./configure
$ make
# make install

You can use ./autogen.sh instead of ./configure you're compiling from
SVN. If you installed any prerequisite language packages using a --prefix
to ./configure, make sure to give the same --prefix to ./configure here.

Testing
===============================================================================

If you are in the source directory after running make, the following
commands should work:

$  echo "TODO test sentence 1" | apertium -d . mar-hin
TODO test translated sentence 1

Files and data
===============================================================================

* apertium-hin-mar.hin-mar.dix  - Bilingual dictionary
* apertium-hin-mar.hin-mar.t1x  - Chunking rules for translating into Hindi
* apertium-hin-mar.mar-hin.t1x  - Chunking rules for translating into Marathi
* apertium-hin-mar.hin-mar.t2x  - Interchunk rules for translating into Hindi
* apertium-hin-mar.mar-hin.t2x  - Interchunk rules for translating into Marathi
* apertium-hin-mar.hin-mar.t3x  - Postchunk rules for translating into Hindi
* apertium-hin-mar.mar-hin.t3x  - Postchunk rules for translating into Marathi
* apertium-hin-mar.hin-mar.lrx  - Lexical selection rules for translating into Hindi
* apertium-hin-mar.mar-hin.lrx  - Lexical selection rules for translating into Marathi
* modes.xml                     - Translation modes

